eatre%20chain%20says%20that%20'Salaar'%20is%20one%20of%20the%20most%20anticipated%20movies%20of%20the%20year..%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fpvrinox-denies-unfair-practices-against-prabhas-starrer-salaar-and-favouring-shah-rukh-khans-dunki-its-one-of-the-most-anticipated-%2Farticleshow%2F106183385.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Is%20the%20European%20Union's%20AI%20Act%20Attempting%20a%20Magna%20Carta%20for%20the%20Digital%20Age%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F30185248%2FUntitled-design-23-2.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20December%209%2C%202023%2C%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20first%20legislation%20on%20AI%20was%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.europarl.europa.eu%2Fnews%2Fen%2Fpress-room%2F20231206IPR15699%2Fartificial-intelligence-act-deal-on-comprehensive-rules-for-trustworthy-ai%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eaccepted%20by%20the%20European%20Parliamen%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3Et%20and%20Council.%20As%20it%20awaits%20ratification%20by%20the%20member%20states%20to%20become%20an%20Act%20to%20be%20implemented%20in%202026%2C%20the%20legal%20ramifications%20of%20the%20Act%20require%2C%20naturally%2C%20more%20discussion%20by%20cybersecurity%20and%20legal%20scholars.%20Flaws%20will%20no%20doubt%20be%20pointed%20out%20and%20weaknesses%20that%20need%20to%20be%20addressed.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThat%20said%2C%20it%20is%20worth%20looking%20at%20the%20draft%20Act%20and%20related%20documents%20as%20an%20important%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Ecultural%20text%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20of%20our%20time%20for%20what%20it%20seeks%20to%20do%2C%20and%20how%20it%20fits%20in%20with%20a%20larger%20emphasis%20on%20rights%20and%20risks%20to%20those%20rights.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20draft%20defines%20AI%20as%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9Csoftware%20that%20is%20developed%20%E2%80%A6%20for%20a%20given%20set%20of%20human-defined%20objectives%2C%20generate%20outputs%20such%20as%20content%2C%20predictions%2C%20recommendations%2C%20or%20decisions%20influencing%20the%20environments%20they%20interact%20with%E2%80%A6%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20insistence%20on%20the%20AI%20as%20fulfilling%20or%20seeking%20to%20fulfil%20%E2%80%98human-defined%20objectives%E2%80%99%20is%20a%20crucial%20one%2C%20because%20it%20assumes%20that%20AIs%20are%20created%20and%20run%20on%20aims%20and%20purposes%20that%20are%20human%20in%20origin.%20Which%20means%2C%20the%20programming%20can%20be%20subject%20to%20the%20same%20biases%20and%20prejudices%20as%20humans%2C%20as%20critics%20such%20as%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dukeupress.edu%2Fcaptivating-technology%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ERuha%20Benjamin%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20have%20noted%2C%20and%20against%20which%20safeguards%20have%20to%20be%20put%20in%20place%20to%20prevent%20discrimination%20and%20harm%20to%20groups%20and%20individuals.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20most%20striking%20aspect%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feur-lex.europa.eu%2Flegal-content%2FEN%2FTXT%2F%3Furi%3Dcelex%253A52021PC0206%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EProposal%20for%20a%20regulation%20of%20the%20European%20parliament%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20and%20of%20the%20council%20laying%20down%20harmonised%20rules%20on%20artificial%20intelligence%20(artificial%20intelligence%20act)%20and%20amending%20certain%20union%20legislative%20acts%E2%80%99%20(the%20proposal%20was%20amended%20extensively%20so%20that%20the%20draft%20expanded%20from%20108%20pages%20to%20350!)%20is%20the%20twin%20poles%20around%20which%20its%20assumptions%20and%20suggestions%20revolve%3A%20rights%20and%20risks.%20The%20very%20first%20objective%20stated%20in%20this%20document%20says%20that%20the%20regulation%20aims%20to%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eensure%20that%20AI%20systems%20placed%20on%20the%20%5BEuropean%5D%20Union%20market%20and%20used%20are%20safe%20and%20respect%20existing%20law%20on%20fundamental%20rights%20and%20Union%20values%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20its%20opening%20statement%20the%20%E2%80%98%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.europarl.europa.eu%2Fdoceo%2Fdocument%2FTA-9-2023-0236_EN.html%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EAmendments%20adopted%20by%20the%20European%20Parliament%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Cspan%3Eon%2014%20June%202023%20on%20the%20proposal%20for%20a%20regulation%20of%20the%20European%20Parliament%20and%20of%20the%20Council%20on%20laying%20down%20harmonised%20rules%20on%20artificial%20intelligence%20(Artificial%20Intelligence%20Act)%20and%20amending%20certain%20Union%20legislative%20acts%E2%80%99%20declares%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20purpose%20of%20this%20Regulation%20is%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cspan%3Eto%20promote%20the%20uptake%20of%20human%20centric%20and%20trustworthy%20artificial%20intelligence%20and%20to%20ensure%20a%20high%20level%20of%20protection%20of%20health%2C%20safety%2C%20fundamental%20rights%2C%20democracy%20and%20rule%20of%20law%20and%20the%20environment%20from%20harmful%20effects%20of%20artificial%20intelligence%20systems%20in%20the%20Union%20while%20supporting%20innovation%20and%20improving%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3E%20the%20functioning%20of%20the%20internal%20market.%E2%80%9D%20%5BEmphasis%20in%20the%20original%5D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThat%20paragraph%20more%20or%20less%20encapsulates%20the%20vision%3A%20trustworthy%20AI%20which%20will%20be%20subjected%20to%20the%20rule%20of%20law%20and%20cannot%20be%20allowed%20to%20disrupt%20foundational%20principles%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Erights%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20and%20has%20to%20be%20human-centric.%20This%20emphasis%20on%20rights%20is%20reiterated%20across%20the%20document%2C%20with%20a%20particular%20inflection%20on%20%E2%80%98the%20fundamental%20rights%20of%20natural%20persons%E2%80%99%2C%20a%20phrase%20the%20draft%20is%20particularly%20keen%20on.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20proposed%20Act%20seeks%20to%20encourage%20the%20production%20of%20and%20innovation%20in%20AI%20technologies%2C%20but%20casts%20them%20within%20a%20risk-and-rights%20framework%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CBy%20laying%20down%20those%20rules%20as%20well%20as%20measures%20in%20support%20of%20innovation%20with%20a%20particular%20focus%20on%20SMEs%20and%20start-ups%2C%20this%20Regulation%20supports%20the%20objective%20of%20promoting%20the%20AI%20made%20in%20Europe%2C%20of%20the%20Union%20of%20being%20a%20global%20leader%20in%20the%20development%20of%20secure%2C%20trustworthy%20and%20ethical%20artificial%20intelligence%2C%20as%20stated%20by%20the%20European%20Council%2C%20and%20it%20ensures%20the%20protection%20of%20ethical%20principles%2C%20as%20specifically%20requested%20by%20the%20European%20Parliament.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20emphasis%20on%20rights%20and%20risk%20is%20very%20welcome%20indeed%20as%20the%20Act%20seeks%20to%20become%20a%20Magna%20Carta%20for%20the%20digital%20era%20wherein%2C%20as%20numerous%20scholars%20have%20pointed%20out%2C%20AI%20threatens%20to%20encroach%20upon%20rights.%20The%20draft%20document%20itself%20makes%20this%20threat%20clear%20when%20it%20writes%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CAside%20from%20the%20many%20beneficial%20uses%20of%20artificial%20intelligence%2C%20that%20technology%20can%20also%20be%20misused%20and%20provide%20novel%20and%20powerful%20tools%20for%20manipulative%2C%20exploitative%20and%20social%20control%20practices.%20Such%20practices%20are%20particularly%20harmful%20and%20abusive%20and%20should%20be%20prohibited%20because%20they%20contradict%20Union%20values%20of%20respect%20for%20human%20dignity%2C%20freedom%2C%20equality%2C%20democracy%20and%20the%20rule%20of%20law%20and%20Union%20fundamental%20rights%2C%20including%20the%20right%20to%20non-discrimination%2C%20data%20protection%20and%20privacy%20and%20the%20rights%20of%20the%20child.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20draft%20document%20categorises%20AI%20in%20terms%20of%20its%20potential%20for%20%E2%80%98low%E2%80%99%20or%20%E2%80%98high%E2%80%99%20risk%2C%20and%20the%20forms%20of%20AI%20that%20belong%20to%20the%20latter%20category%20are%20important%20for%20their%20potential%20to%20directly%20or%20indirectly%20impinge%20on%20rights.%20Later%20it%20defines%20what%20it%20means%20by%20high-risk%20AI%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9Cit%20is%20appropriate%20to%20classify%20them%20as%20high-risk%20if%2C%20in%20the%20light%20of%20their%20intended%20purpose%2C%20they%20pose%20a%20significant%20risk%20of%20harm%20to%20the%20health%20and%20safety%20or%20the%20fundamental%20rights%20of%20persons.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%20list%20of%20high-risk%20AI%2C%20the%20draft%20regulations%20seek%20a%20ban%20on%20%E2%80%98systems%20with%20the%20objective%20to%20or%20the%20effect%20of%20materially%20distorting%20human%20behaviour%2C%20whereby%20physical%20or%20psychological%20harms%20are%20likely%20to%20occur%E2%80%99.%20It%20goes%20on%20to%20define%20these%20systems%20in%20some%20detail%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9Cneuro-technologies%20assisted%20by%20AI%20systems%20that%20are%20used%20to%20monitor%2C%20use%2C%20or%20influence%20neural%20data%20gathered%20through%20brain-computer%20interfaces%20insofar%20as%20they%20are%20materially%20distorting%20the%20behaviour%20of%20a%20natural%20person%20in%20a%20manner%20that%20causes%20or%20is%20likely%20to%20cause%20that%20person%20or%20another%20person%20significant%20harm.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThat%20is%2C%20human%20behaviour%20cannot%20be%20subject%20to%20AI%20control%20%E2%80%93%20the%20stuff%20of%20sci-fi%2C%20of%20course%20%E2%80%93%20and%20any%20such%20interventionary%20systems%20should%20be%20banned.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMoving%20from%20behaviour%20to%20identification%20of%20group%20behaviour%2C%20the%20document%20makes%20a%20case%20for%20both%20individuals%20and%20members%20of%20a%20group%20where%20an%20AI%20system%20may%20%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eperceive%20or%20exploit%20vulnerabilities%20of%20individuals%20and%20specific%20groups%20of%20persons%20due%20to%20their%20known%20or%20predicted%20personality%20traits%2C%20age%2C%20physical%20or%20mental%20incapacities%2C%20social%20or%20economic%20situation%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EProceeding%20from%20the%20above%20awareness%20to%20the%20exploitation%20of%20vulnerabilities%2C%20the%20draft%20regulations%20then%20worry%20about%20AI%20being%20used%20to%20foster%20or%20reinforce%20discrimination%20of%20social%20groups%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CAI%20systems%20that%20categorise%20natural%20persons%20by%20assigning%20them%20to%20specific%20categories%2C%20according%20to%20known%20or%20inferred%20sensitive%20or%20protected%20characteristics%20are%20particularly%20intrusive%2C%20violate%20human%20dignity%20and%20hold%20great%20risk%20of%20discrimination.%20Such%20characteristics%20include%20gender%2C%20gender%20identity%2C%20race%2C%20ethnic%20origin%2C%20migration%20or%20citizenship%20status%2C%20political%20orientation%2C%20sexual%20orientation%2C%20religion%2C%20disability%20or%20any%20other%20grounds%20on%20which%20discrimination%20is%20prohibited%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EClearly%20then%2C%20the%20AI%20Act%20in%20its%20draft%20%E2%80%93%20the%20final%20version%20has%20not%20been%20published%20yet%20%E2%80%93%20is%20keenly%20alive%20to%20the%20social%20and%20cultural%20dimensions%2C%20from%20discrimination%20to%20social%20sorting%20to%20privacy.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20makes%20it%20topical%2C%20necessary%20and%20in%20line%20with%20the%20most%20dominant%20%E2%80%93%20at%20least%20in%20the%20Global%20North%2C%20let%20us%20face%20it%20%E2%80%93%20discourse%20of%20the%20age%3A%20that%20of%20Human%20Rights.%20It%20also%20shows%20an%20awareness%20of%20historical%20wrongs%20and%20systemic%20injustices%20that%20have%20disenfranchised%20particular%20groups%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CWhen%20improperly%20designed%20and%20used%2C%20such%20systems%20can%20be%20particularly%20intrusive%20and%20may%20violate%20the%20right%20to%20education%20and%20training%20as%20well%20as%20the%20right%20not%20to%20be%20discriminated%20against%20and%20perpetuate%20historical%20patterns%20of%20discrimination%2C%20for%20example%20against%20women%2C%20certain%20age%20groups%2C%20persons%20with%20disabilities%2C%20or%20persons%20of%20certain%20racial%20or%20ethnic%20origins%20or%20sexual%20orientation.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F15194710%2Fpexels-freestocksorg-113885.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F15194710%2Fpexels-freestocksorg-113885.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F15194710%2Fpexels-freestocksorg-113885-300x200.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F15194710%2Fpexels-freestocksorg-113885-1024x683.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-689377%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22800%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EThe%20European%20Union%20Flag.%20Photo%3A%20Pexels%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20this%20awareness%20of%20historical%20risks%20and%20current%20risks%20and%20the%20concern%20over%20rights%2C%20the%20draft%20Act%20is%20in%20tune%20with%20what%20commentators%20like%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnyupress.org%2F9781479837243%2Falgorithms-of-oppression%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ESafiya%20Umoja%20Noble%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20predict%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CArtificial%20intelligence%20will%20become%20a%20major%20human%20rights%20issue%20in%20the%20twenty-first%20century.%20We%20are%20only%20beginning%20to%20understand%20the%20long-term%20consequences%20of%20these%20decision-making%20tools%20in%20both%20masking%20and%20deepening%20social%20inequality.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20draft%20document%20echoes%20Noble%20and%20others%20when%20it%20writes%3A%20%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EAI%20systems%20providing%20social%20scoring%20of%20natural%20persons%20for%20general%20purpose%20may%20lead%20to%20discriminatory%20outcomes%20and%20the%20exclusion%20of%20certain%20groups%E2%80%A6%20Such%20AI%20systems%20should%20be%20therefore%20prohibited.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESocial%20sorting%20even%20for%20law%20enforcement%20purposes%20is%20a%20grave%20risk%2C%20and%20AI%20which%20makes%20this%20easy%20%E2%80%93%20and%20carries%2C%20let%20us%20emphasize%2C%20the%20same%20racial%2C%20sexist%20and%20ethnic%20biases%20that%20humans%20possess%20and%20exercise%20(the%20%E2%80%98human-defined%20objectives%E2%80%99%20which%20the%20draft%20states%20very%20early)%20%E2%80%93%20should%20be%20prohibited%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CAI%20systems%20used%20by%20law%20enforcement%20authorities%20or%20on%20their%20behalf%20to%20make%20predictions%2C%20profiles%20or%20risk%20assessments%20based%20on%20profiling%20of%20natural%20persons%20or%20data%20analysis%20based%20on%20personality%20traits%20and%20characteristics%2C%20including%20the%20person%E2%80%99s%20location%2C%20or%20past%20criminal%20behaviour%20of%20natural%20persons%20or%20groups%20of%20persons%20for%20the%20purpose%20of%20predicting%20the%20occurrence%20or%20reoccurrence%20of%20an%20actual%20or%20potential%20criminal%20offence(s)%20or%20other%20criminalised%20social%20behaviour%20or%20administrative%20offences%2C%20including%20fraud%20prediction%20systems%2C%20hold%20a%20particular%20risk%20of%20discrimination%20against%20certain%20persons%20or%20groups%20of%20persons%2C%20as%20they%20violate%20human%20dignity%20as%20well%20as%20the%20key%20legal%20principle%20of%20presumption%20of%20innocence.%20Such%20AI%20systems%20should%20therefore%20be%20prohibited.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEven%20CCTV%20and%20surveillance%20systems%20that%20have%20been%20put%20in%20place%20%E2%80%98to%20create%20or%20expand%20facial%20recognition%20databases%20add%20to%20the%20feeling%20of%20mass%20surveillance%20and%20can%20lead%20to%20gross%20violations%20of%20fundamental%20rights%2C%20including%20the%20right%20to%20privacy%E2%80%99%20should%20be%20prohibited%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Act.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20draft%20Act%20also%20worries%20about%20the%20now%20ubiquitous%20biometric%20identification%20and%20databasing%20determines%20access%20to%20public%20spaces%2C%20and%20so%20wants%20these%20regulated%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20use%20of%20AI%20systems%20for%20%E2%80%98real-time%E2%80%99%20remote%20biometric%20identification%20of%20natural%20persons%20in%20publicly%20accessible%20spaces%20is%20particularly%20intrusive%20to%20the%20rights%20and%20freedoms%20of%20the%20concerned%20persons%E2%80%A6%20The%20use%20of%20those%20systems%20in%20publicly%20accessible%20places%20should%20therefore%20be%20prohibited.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHere%20it%20has%20accounted%20for%20the%20right%20to%20privacy%20and%20the%20right%20to%20public%20spaces.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20AI%20Act%20also%20worries%20that%20the%20systems%20will%20monitor%20humans%20as%20never%20before%3A%20%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EAI%20systems%20intended%20to%20be%20used%20%E2%80%A6%20to%20detect%20the%20emotional%20state%20of%20individuals%20should%20be%20prohibited.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Act%20then%20lists%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Eall%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20the%20rights%20that%20must%20be%20guarded%20from%20what%20it%20terms%20%E2%80%98high-risk%E2%80%99%20AI%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9Cthe%20right%20to%20human%20dignity%2C%20respect%20for%20private%20and%20family%20life%2C%20protection%20of%20personal%20data%2C%20freedom%20of%20expression%20and%20information%2C%20freedom%20of%20assembly%20and%20of%20association%2C%20and%20non-discrimination%2C%20right%20to%20education%20consumer%20protection%2C%20workers%E2%80%99%20rights%2C%20rights%20of%20persons%20with%20disabilities%2C%20gender%20equality%2C%20intellectual%20property%20rights%2C%20right%20to%20an%20effective%20remedy%20and%20to%20a%20fair%20trial%2C%20right%20of%20defence%20and%20the%20presumption%20of%20innocence%2C%20right%20to%20good%20administration.%20In%20addition%20to%20those%20rights%2C%20it%20is%20important%20to%20highlight%20that%20children%20have%20specific%20rights%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20then%20identifies%20domains%20in%20which%20the%20deployment%20of%20AI%2C%20without%20regulation%20and%20appropriate%20safety%20measures%2C%20can%20produce%20harm%3A%20education%2C%20employment%2C%20health%20care%20services%2C%20law%20enforcement%20processes%20where%20it%20may%20%E2%80%98affect%20the%20lives%20or%20the%20fundamental%20rights%20of%20individuals%E2%80%99%2C%20the%20%E2%80%98fields%20of%20migration%2C%20asylum%20and%20border%20control%20management%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhen%20we%20think%20of%20how%20already%20existing%20systems%20have%20produced%20additional%20forms%20and%20degrees%20of%20discrimination%2C%20the%20Act%E2%80%99s%20concerns%20appear%20legitimate.%20To%20take%20just%20one%20example%2C%20systems%20such%20as%20Correctional%20Offender%20Management%20Profiling%20for%20Alternative%20Sanctions%20(COMPAS)%2C%20studies%20demonstrate%2C%20were%20built%20to%20make%20the%20judicial%20processes%20more%20objective%20and%20therefore%2C%20by%20implication%2C%20more%20just.%20Law%20enforcement%20authorities%20administered%20a%20questionnaire%20to%20those%20people%20who%20had%20been%20arrested%2C%20and%20their%20responses%20fed%20into%20a%20computer.%20COMPAS%20then%20%E2%80%98predicted%E2%80%99%20how%20likely%20the%20person%20was%20to%20commit%20a%20crime%20in%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Efuture%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20These%20scores%20and%20predictions%20were%20submitted%20to%20the%20judiciary%2C%20ostensibly%20making%20their%20rulings%20founded%20on%20data.%20The%20ironic%20horror%20was%20that%20it%20resulted%20in%20African%20Americans%20receiving%20longer%20jail%20sentences%20than%20white%20persons.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20draft%20Act%20is%20thus%20alert%20to%20biases%20in%20the%20datasets%20and%20the%20process%20of%20databasing%2C%20and%20calls%20for%3A%20%E2%80%98specific%20attention%20to%20the%20mitigation%20of%20possible%20biases%20in%20the%20datasets%2C%20that%20might%20lead%20to%20risks%20to%20fundamental%20rights%20or%20discriminatory%20outcomes%20for%20the%20persons%20affected%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cspan%3EHere%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cspan%3Eit%20again%20implicitly%20signals%20machine%20bias%20that%20stems%20from%20%E2%80%98human-defined%20objectives%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMachine%20biases%20such%20as%20COMPAS%2C%20the%20data-based%20predictive%20systems%20whether%20in%20migration%2Fcrime%20control%20or%20calculations%20of%20creditworthiness%20emerge%20not%20from%20the%20machines%20but%20their%20programming%20by%20humans.%20As%20Meredith%20Broussard%20puts%20it%20in%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmitpress.mit.edu%2F9780262537018%2Fartificial-unintelligence%2F%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EArtificial%20Unintelligence%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CWhen%20you%20believe%20that%20a%20decision%20generated%20by%20a%20computer%20is%20better%20or%20fairer%20than%20a%20decision%20generated%20by%20a%20human%2C%20you%20stop%20questioning%20the%20validity%20of%20the%20inputs%20to%20the%20system.%20It%E2%80%99s%20easy%20to%20forget%20the%20principle%20of%20garbage%20in%2C%20garbage%20out%E2%80%94especially%20if%20you%20really%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ewant%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ethe%20computer%20to%20be%20correct.%20It%E2%80%99s%20important%20to%20question%20whether%20these%20algorithms%2C%20and%20the%20people%20who%20make%20them%2C%20are%20making%20the%20world%20better%20or%20worse.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20draft%20Act%20document%20in%20itself%20isn%E2%80%99t%20trying%20to%20wind%20us%20up%20and%20make%20us%20even%20more%20paranoid%20than%20we%20are%20(if%20we%20are%20not%20paranoid%2C%20then%20something%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Eis%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20wrong%20with%20us%2C%20ain%E2%80%99t%20that%20so%3F).%20Its%20focus%2C%20as%20it%20states%2C%20is%20to%20alert%20us%20to%20the%20%E2%80%98reasonably%20foreseeable%20misuse%20of%20the%20system%E2%80%99%20which%20is%20what%20literary%20and%20cultural%20texts%2C%20particularly%20sci-fi%20and%20apocalyptic%20works%2C%20do.%20This%20is%20why%20the%20draft%20document%20is%20a%20major%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Ecultural%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20document%20of%20the%20age.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIf%2C%20as%20commentators%20fear%2C%20%E2%80%98technological%20redlining%E2%80%99%20(Safiya%20Umoja%20Noble%E2%80%99s%20term%20for%20digital%20racial%20profiling)%20is%20widespread%2C%20and%20rights%20will%20be%20increasingly%20encroached%20upon%2C%20then%20the%20AI%20Act%2C%20albeit%20restricted%20to%20the%20European%20Union%2C%20for%20now%2C%20is%20going%20a%20considerable%20way%20to%20assuage%20the%20fears%2C%20manage%20the%20anxieties%20and%20regulate%20what%20AI%20can%20be%20permitted%20to%20do.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWe%20are%20aware%20of%20surveillance%2C%20from%20WhatsApp%20to%20commercial%20service%20providers%2C%20the%20tracking%20of%20Aadhaar%20and%20bank%20accounts%2C%20most%20of%20this%20enabled%20by%20an%20Orwellian%20state%20that%20then%20also%20powers%20not%20just%20targeted%20advertising%20but%20also%20misinformation%20and%20the%20infocalypse%20of%20hate%20that%20is%20addressed%20to%20specific%20groups.%20AI%2C%20as%20the%20documents%20cited%20suggest%2C%20will%20amplify%20this%20scenario%20many%20times%20over.%20Whether%20governments%20across%20the%20world%20choose%20to%20acknowledge%2C%20and%20employ%2C%20the%20risks-and-rights%20mode%20as%20the%20EU%20Act%20seeks%20to%20do%2C%20or%20merely%20sit%20back%20and%20allow%20more%20inequities%20to%20enter%20the%20system%20remains%20to%20be%20seen.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fpramod-k-nayar%5C%22%3EPramod%20K.%20Nayar%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0teaches%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Hyderabad.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703156716000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F30185248%2FUntitled-desi