's%20body%20that%20could%20claim%20us%20first.%3Cp%3ETyler%20Le%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EPageland%20Lane%20is%20a%20roughly%205-mile-long%2C%20one-lane%20road%20in%20Prince%20William%20County%2C%20Virginia%2C%20an%20hour%20south%20of%20Washington%2C%20DC.%20To%20the%20east%20it%20hugs%20Manassas%20National%20Battlefield%20Park%3B%20to%20the%20west%20lie%20thousands%20of%20acres%C2%A0dotted%20sporadically%20with%20homes%20and%20miles%20of%20pristine%20farmland%2C%20with%20grazing%20horses%20and%20tight%20round%20hay%20bales%20lazing%20in%20the%20sun.%20It%20all%20looks%20plucked%20from%20a%20postcard.%20It's%20also%2C%20Elena%20Schlossberg%20repeatedly%20reminded%20me%20while%20driving%20me%20on%20a%20tour%20of%20the%20area%2C%20very%20likely%20doomed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20past%20few%20years%2C%20this%20community%20next%20to%20one%20of%20America's%20most%20historic%20battlegrounds%20has%20been%20the%20site%20of%20a%20new%20kind%20of%20civil%20war.%20Two%20deep-pocketed%20tech%20companies%2C%20QTS%20and%20Compass%2C%20are%20seeking%20to%20cover%20some%202%2C100%20acres%20of%20rural%20land%20with%2023%20million%20square%20feet%20of%20data%20centers%20%E2%80%94%20one%20of%20the%20largest%20such%20developments%20in%20the%20world.%20Just%20what%20they'll%20be%20used%20for%20%E2%80%94%20cloud%20storage%2C%20AI%2C%20or%20otherwise%20%E2%80%94%20is%20still%20an%20open%20question.%20But%20by%20some%20estimates%2C%20the%20Prince%20William%20County%20Digital%20Gateway%2C%20as%20the%20project%20is%20known%2C%20would%20suck%20up%20as%20much%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pecva.org%2Fwork%2Fenergy-work%2Fdata-centers%2Fputting-the-pieces-together-on-digital-gateway%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E3%20gigawatts%20of%20energy%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%C2%A0enough%20to%20power%20millions%20of%20homes%20around%20the%20clock.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Schlossberg%2C%20a%20self-proclaimed%20%26quot%3Bbig-mouth%20mom%26quot%3B%20who%20runs%20the%20grassroots%20group%20Coalition%20to%20Protect%20Prince%20William%20County%2C%20the%20Digital%20Gateway%20represents%20not%20just%20an%20invasive%20eyesore%20but%20also%20an%20existential%20threat.%20All%20over%20the%20world%2C%20data%20centers%20are%20multiplying%20at%20record%20rates%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0and%20growing%20bigger%20and%20more%20power-hungry%20by%20the%20year.%20Inside%20their%20boxy%20bellies%20is%20the%20lifeblood%20of%20the%20internet%2C%20miles%20of%20cables%20connected%20to%20racks%20of%20computers%20that%20fuel%20our%20telehealth%20appointments%20and%20family%20group%20chats%2C%20our%20Netflix%20binges%20and%20Google%20Docs.%20In%20the%20process%2C%20data%20centers%20gorge%20on%20electricity%20and%20guzzle%20exorbitant%20amounts%20of%20water%20to%20keep%20cool%2C%20often%20overburdening%20local%20power%20grids%20and%20water%20supplies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20arms%20race%20over%20artificial%20intelligence%2C%C2%A0which%20runs%20on%20special%20chips%20that%20suck%20up%20even%20more%20energy%2C%C2%A0has%20accelerated%20the%20boom.%20In%20the%20first%20half%20of%202023%2C%20North%20America%20set%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cbre.com%2Finsights%2Freports%2Fnorth-america-data-center-trends-h1-2023%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecord%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20data-center%20construction%2C%20up%2025%25%20in%20the%20top%20eight%20markets.%20And%20that's%20just%20for%20data%20centers%20that%20lease%20out%20server%20space%20to%20other%20businesses.%20Tech%20giants%20such%20as%20Google%2C%20Microsoft%2C%20Amazon%2C%20and%20Meta%20%E2%80%94%20so-called%20hyperscalers%20%E2%80%94%20are%20spending%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvirginia-data-center-boom-power-grid-utility-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebillions%20of%20dollars%3C%2Fa%3E%20more%20to%20build%20out%20their%20own%20data%20centers.%20Jensen%20Huang%2C%20the%20CEO%20of%20the%20AI-chip%20giant%20Nvidia%2C%20predicts%20that%20in%20the%20next%20four%20years%20alone%2C%20companies%20will%20spend%20%241%20trillion%20to%20add%20to%20their%20arsenal%20of%20data%20centers%20%E2%80%94%20creating%20what%20Blackstone%2C%20one%20of%20the%20world's%20largest%20asset%20managers%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sec.gov%2FArchives%2Fedgar%2Fdata%2F1662972%2F000119312523196177%2Fd515874d8k.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecalls%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20%26quot%3Bonce-in-a-generation%20engine%20for%20future%20growth%20in%20data%20centers.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20that%20growth%20may%20come%20at%20a%20steep%20cost.%20At%20the%20heart%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdata-centers-ai-artificial-intelligence-farmland-power-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edata-center%20boom%3C%2Fa%3E%20lies%20a%20strange%20paradox%3A%20The%20more%20the%20internet%20has%20consumed%20our%20lived%20reality%2C%20the%20easier%20it's%20been%20to%20ignore%20the%20physical%20infrastructure%20required%20to%20power%20that%20reality.%20Today%2C%20the%20complexity%20of%20the%20large%20language%20models%20being%20developed%20by%20OpenAI%2C%20Google%2C%20and%20Meta%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0and%20the%20frenzy%20to%20bake%20those%20models%20into%20everything%20from%20Google%20Search%20to%20Facebook%20stickers%20to%20%26quot%3BHarry%20Potter%26quot%3B%20fan%20fiction%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0is%20forcing%20more%20and%20more%20Americans%20like%20Schlossberg%20to%20confront%20the%20high%20price%20of%20our%20digital%20addiction.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20need%20to%20know%20that%20every%20picture%2C%20every%20TED%20Talk%2C%20every%20Instagram%2C%20everything%20they%20save%20is%20going%20into%20a%20concrete%20box%20that%20requires%20power%2C%26quot%3B%20Schlossberg%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20free%2C%20and%20it's%20not%20ethereal%2C%20and%20it's%20not%20fluffy.%26quot%3B%20For%20all%20of%20the%20fears%20about%20AI's%20brain%20%E2%80%94%20that%20chatbots%20will%20steal%20our%20jobs%20or%20somehow%20destroy%20humanity%20as%20we%20know%20it%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20AI's%20body%20that%20could%20claim%20us%20first.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20most%20of%20human%20history%2C%20doing%20almost%20anything%20required%20having%20and%20storing%20a%20lot%20of%20stuff.%20Books%20to%20access%20information.%20A%20Rolodex%20to%20call%20clients.%20Vinyl%2C%20then%20tapes%2C%20then%20CDs%20to%20play%20music.%20Dusty%20photo%20albums%20to%20recall%20old%20memories%2C%20and%20bulging%20filing%20cabinets%20to%20retrieve%20old%20invoices.%20For%20the%20most%20part%2C%20we%20knew%20where%20our%20stuff%20lived%20because%2C%20for%20the%20most%20part%2C%20it%20lived%20with%20us.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20internet%20came%20along%2C%20a%20lot%20of%20that%20stuff%20seemed%20to%20disappear.%20It%20was%20stored%20somewhere%20we%20called%20the%20cloud%2C%20an%20abstract%2C%20celestial%20space%20where%20we%20never%20had%20to%20clean%20out%20our%20closets%20and%20that%20miraculously%20delivered%20our%20stuff%20to%20us%20with%20a%20click%20or%20a%20swipe%20or%20no%20prompting%20at%20all.%20%26quot%3BYou%20have%20a%20new%20memory%2C%26quot%3B%20our%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcategory%2Fiphone%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EiPhones%3C%2Fa%3E%20tell%20us.%20At%20first%2C%20the%20transition%20was%20disorienting.%20People%20grasped%20for%20some%20understanding%20of%20how%20the%20internet%20physically%20functioned.%20In%20a%20now%20classic%20segment%20of%20the%20%26quot%3BToday%26quot%3B%20show%20in%201994%2C%20the%20befuddled%20hosts%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DUlJku_CSyNg%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epuzzled%3C%2Fa%3E%20over%20how%20email%20worked.%20%26quot%3BWhat%2C%20do%20you%20write%20to%20it%2C%20like%20mail%3F%26quot%3B%20Bryant%20Gumbel%20asked.%20%26quot%3BAllison%2C%20can%20you%20explain%20what%20internet%20is%3F%26quot%3B%20Katie%20Couric%20pleaded%20with%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fblogs%2Fpost-partisan%2Fwp%2F2015%2F02%2F11%2Fallison-can-you-explain-what-internet-is%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eapparently%20tech-savvy%3C%2Fa%3E%20off-camera%20producer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22data%20center%20farmland%20neighborhood%20amazon%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64b97ccf4182d800196a4bf6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22683%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EIn%20Data%20Center%20Alley%2C%20on%20what%20was%20recently%20Virginia%20farmland%2C%20Amazon%20and%20other%20tech%20giants%20have%20erected%20some%20200%20data%20centers%20%E2%80%94%20some%20right%20next%20to%20residential%20homes.%3Cp%3EJahi%20Chikwendiu%2FThe%20Washington%20Post%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20today%2C%20three%20decades%20later%2C%20how%20many%20of%20us%20could%20actually%20explain%20to%20Couric%20%26quot%3Bwhat%20internet%20is%26quot%3B%3F%20As%20the%20web%20became%20the%20water%20we%20all%20swim%20in%2C%20the%20impulse%20to%20ask%2C%20%26quot%3BWhat%20the%20hell%20is%20water%3F%26quot%3B%20disappeared.%20At%20a%20certain%20point%2C%20it%20all%20just%20started%20to%20feel%20invisible.%20And%20perhaps%20no%20technological%20advancement%20of%20the%20past%20few%20decades%20has%20felt%20like%20more%20of%20a%20magic%20trick%20than%20generative%20AI.%20Type%20a%20prompt%20into%20ChatGPT%20and%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0%3Cem%3Ealakazam!%20%E2%80%94%3C%2Fem%3E%20it%20will%20just%20as%20easily%20spit%20out%20a%20five-year%20plan%20for%20your%20fintech%20startup%20as%20it%20will%20a%20bedtime%20story%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fboomer-grandparents-gift-junk-grandkids-millennial-parents-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESanta%20Claus'%3C%2Fa%3E%20first%20visit%20to%20the%20moon%2C%20written%20in%20the%20style%20of%20Upton%20Sinclair.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELike%20any%20good%20magic%20trick%2C%20the%20internet%20is%20based%20on%20an%20illusion.%20Our%20stuff%20hasn't%20vanished%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0it's%20just%20moved%20to%20data%20centers.%20Crammed%20with%20everything%20we%20once%20kept%20close%20at%20hand%2C%20these%20massive%20storage%20facilities%20fill%20campuses%20the%20size%20of%20small%20villages%20and%20are%20powered%20by%20squat%20substations%20that%20occupy%20even%20more%20land%2C%20which%20are%20connected%20to%20lengthy%20transmission%20lines%20that%20funnel%20power%20from%20faraway%20coal%20plants%2C%20nuclear%20facilities%2C%20solar%20farms%2C%20or%20whatever%20source%20it%20takes%20to%20satiate%20their%20increasingly%20voracious%20appetites.%20And%20AI%20data%20centers%20are%20the%20hungriest%20of%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETraining%20generative-AI%20models%20requires%20special%20chips%20called%20graphics%20processing%20units%20or%20tensor%20processing%20units%2C%20which%20are%20better%20at%20multitasking%20and%20pack%20significantly%20more%20computing%20power%20into%20a%20smaller%20footprint.%20But%20the%20data%20centers%20that%20rely%20on%20those%20chips%20consume%20massive%20amounts%20of%20energy%2C%20even%20by%20internet%20standards.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.energy.gov%2Feere%2Fbuildings%2Fdata-centers-and-servers%23%3A~%3Atext%3DCollectively%252C%2520these%2520spaces%2520account%2520for%2Cenergy%2520use%2520in%2520data%2520centers.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAccording%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20the%20Department%20of%20Energy%2C%20traditional%20data%20centers%20already%20use%20up%20to%2050%20times%20as%20much%20energy%20as%20a%20typical%20office%20building%2C%20accounting%20for%202%25%20of%20America's%20electricity%20use.%20Server%20racks%20dedicated%20to%20training%20generative%20AI%2C%20by%20contrast%2C%20may%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.spglobal.com%2Fmarketintelligence%2Fen%2Fnews-insights%2Flatest-news-headlines%2Fpower-of-ai-surging-datacenter-load-has-dominion-bracing-for-ai-s-added-demand-77792886%23%3A~%3Atext%3DAI%2520implications%26amp%3Btext%3Dsomewhere%2520between%2520five%2520and%2520seven%2CCPUs%2520to%2520graphics%2520processing%2520units.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erequire%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20much%20as%20seven%20times%20the%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3Eenergy%20as%20traditional%20server%20racks%20do.%20When%20it%20comes%20to%20power%20use%2C%20AI%20is%20the%20internet%20on%20hyperdrive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20then%20there's%20the%20demand%20from%20us%20users.%20Any%20time%20we%20ask%20a%20chatbot%20to%20plan%20our%20vacation%2C%20solve%20our%20calculus%20homework%2C%20or%20make%20us%20a%20meme%2C%20we're%20asking%20a%20data%20center%20to%20tap%20more%20power%20than%20we'd%20use%20doing%20a%20web%20search%20for%20the%20same%20stuff.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.technologyreview.com%2F2023%2F12%2F01%2F1084189%2Fmaking-an-image-with-generative-ai-uses-as-much-energy-as-charging-your-phone%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EResearch%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20found%20making%20even%20a%20single%20image%20with%20generative-AI%20tools%20can%20use%20as%20much%20energy%20as%20fully%20charging%20your%20cellphone.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20this%20demand%20is%20creating%20energy%20bottlenecks.%20%26quot%3BThat%20power%20capacity%20isn't%20just%20sitting%20out%20there%20available%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Jon%20Lin%2C%20an%20executive%20vice%20president%20at%20Equinix%2C%20which%20operates%20data%20centers%20in%2032%20countries.%20Indeed%2C%20in%20a%20recent%20Cisco%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cisco.com%2Fc%2Fm%2Fen_us%2Fsolutions%2Fai%2Freadiness-index.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esurvey%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%2097%25%20of%20business%20leaders%20say%20they're%20feeling%20pressure%20to%20implement%20an%20AI%20strategy%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0but%20more%20than%20half%20don't%20feel%20they're%20fully%20prepared%20to%20meet%20the%20necessary%20power%20demands.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFaced%20with%20this%20pressure%2C%20local%20utility%20companies%20are%20making%20tough%20environmental%20trade-offs.%20Virginia's%20Dominion%20Energy%20recently%20predicted%20electricity%20demands%20in%20its%20service%20area%20would%20nearly%20double%20in%20the%20next%2015%20years%2C%20an%20unprecedented%20growth%20rate%20that%20the%20utility%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn-dominionenergy-prd-001.azureedge.net%2F-%2Fmedia%2Fpdfs%2Fglobal%2Fcompany%2F2023-va-integrated-resource-plan.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eattributed%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20at%20least%20in%20part%2C%20to%20data%20centers.%20Amazon%20alone%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-data-centers-energy-grid-electricity-virginia-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eplans%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20invest%20%2435%20billion%20in%20data%20centers%20in%20Virginia%2C%20adding%20to%20the%20%2452%20billion%20it's%20already%20spent%20there.%20(Full%20disclosure%3A%20I'm%20married%20to%20an%20Amazon%20employee.)%20To%20keep%20up%20with%20power%20demands%2C%20Dominion%20says%20that%20while%2095%25%20of%20its%20new%20power%20plants%20will%20be%20carbon-free%2C%20it%20will%20also%20need%20to%20build%20new%20gas-powered%20plants%20and%20keep%20some%20fossil%20fuel%20plants%20that%20were%20set%20to%20be%20retired%20operating%20for%20far%20longer%20than%20expected.%20The%20utility%20now%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Frichmond.com%2Fnews%2Fstate-regional%2Fgovernment-politics%2Fdominion-plan-sees-carbon-emissions-rising-as-electric-use-soars%2Farticle_f360cf80-25aa-11ee-ae70-d3d88081eeaa.html%23%3A~%3Atext%3DTwo%2520options%2520Dominion%2520detailed%2520in%2C65%2525%2520increase%2520in%2520carbon%2520emissions.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epredicts%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20in%2025%20years%2C%20its%20carbon%20emissions%20will%20be%2065%25%20higher%20than%20it%20was%20expecting%20just%20two%20years%20ago%2C%20but%20Dominion%20says%20those%20estimates%20are%20subject%20to%20change.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESuch%20constraints%20are%20likely%20to%20push%20data%20centers%20into%20new%20pastures%20%E2%80%94%20literally.%20Google%20plans%20to%20spend%20%241.2%20billion%20to%20build%20its%20fleet%20of%20centers%20in%20Nebraska%20to%20capitalize%20on%20the%20state's%20wind%20power.%20Microsoft%20similarly%20opened%20data%20centers%20in%20Sweden%20because%20of%20the%20country's%20ability%20to%20provide%20plenty%20of%20clean%20energy.%20%26quot%3BWe%20are%20spreading%20out%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Noelle%20Walsh%2C%20the%20corporate%20vice%20president%20of%20cloud%20and%20innovation%20for%20Microsoft.%20%26quot%3BWe're%20going%20to%20where%20the%20customers%20are%20but%20also%20going%20to%20where%20the%20resources%20are%20as%20well.%26quot%3B%20Of%20course%2C%20the%20industry's%20growth%20in%20new%20territories%20also%20means%20more%20communities%20are%20about%20to%20be%20exposed%20to%20data-center%20sprawl%2C%20and%20its%20consequences.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20show%20me%20what%20that%20conquest%20looks%20like%2C%20Schlossberg%20drove%20me%2025%20miles%20north%20of%20Pageland%20Lane%20to%20Data%20Center%20Alley%20in%20Loudoun%20County%2C%20Virginia.%20The%20area%20bursts%20with%20the%20largest%20concentration%20of%20data%20centers%20on%20earth%2C%20underpinning%20vast%20amounts%20of%20the%20world's%20internet%20traffic.%20As%20we%20tooled%20around%20in%20her%20Ford%20Fusion%2C%20every%20corner%20revealed%20another%20imposing%20gray%20cube%20with%20a%20corporate%20logo%20emblazoned%20on%20the%20side%2C%20stretching%20across%20tens%20or%20hundreds%20of%20thousands%20of%20square%20feet.%20These%20beasts%20can%20be%20noisy%20neighbors%2C%20too.%20%26quot%3BDataCenter%20is%20generating%20noise%20like%20a%20freight%20train%20all%20night%20long%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20one%20of%20more%20than%2040%20complaints%20to%20Loudoun%20County%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdata-center-noise-disruptions-loudoun-county-virginia-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%20obtained%20through%20public%20records%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BConstant%20humming%20noise%20like%20a%20lawn%20mower%20outside%2024%2F7%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20another.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20be%20sure%2C%20many%20residents%20in%20Prince%20William%20County%20favor%20the%20arrival%20of%20data%20centers.%20Proponents%20of%20the%20Digital%20Gateway%20development%20argue%20that%20it%20would%20generate%20an%20estimated%20%24400%20million%20in%20tax%20revenues%20a%20year%20for%20the%20county.%20In%20Loudoun%20County%2C%20data%20centers%20brought%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dcnewsnow.com%2Fnews%2Flocal-news%2Fvirginia%2Floudoun-county%2Fin-northern-virginia-growing-data-center-revenue-is-volatile-tax-records-show%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%24663%20million%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20taxes%20last%20year%2C%20accounting%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.vpm.org%2F2023-10-19%2Fvirginia-is-the-worlds-data-center-hub-but-whats-the-cost%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eone-third%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20county's%20annual%20budget.%20All%20told%2C%20according%20to%20industry%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsilkstart.s3.amazonaws.com%2F24d65794-e6d9-42ab-8d73-fd7c0f82fe72.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eestimates%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20construction%20and%20operation%20of%20data%20centers%20in%20the%20U.S.%20generated%20nearly%20%24100%20billion%20in%20federal%2C%20state%2C%20and%20local%20tax%20revenue%20in%202021%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0helping%20to%20fund%20schools%2C%20parks%2C%20and%20other%20essential%20infrastructure.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat's%20a%20pretty%20good%20return%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Terry%20Clower%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20public%20policy%20at%20George%20Mason%20University.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20didn't%20have%20the%20data%20centers%2C%20then%20you'd%20probably%20have%20a%20combination%20of%20both%20lower%20services%20being%20offered%20and%20higher%20tax%20rates.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBesides%2C%20it's%20not%20as%20if%20the%20area%20is%20untouched%20by%20data%20centers.%20It's%20already%20home%20to%20dozens%20of%20them.%20In%20fact%2C%20it%20was%20local%20landowners%20who%20conceived%20of%20the%20Digital%20Gateway%20to%20begin%20with%2C%20after%20the%20industry's%20growth%20throughout%20Northern%20Virginia%20began%20to%20creep%20into%20their%20backyards.%20%26quot%3BWe%20decided%20we%20needed%20to%20create%20our%20destiny%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Mary%20Ann%20Ghadban%2C%20a%20local%20resident%20and%20real-estate%20broker%20who%20handled%20a%20portion%20of%20the%20project.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223400%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Manassas%20National%20Battlefield%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65830881cefc010bea258000%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222178%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Digital%20Gateway%20project%20in%20Virginia%20aims%20to%20cover%20some%202%2C100%20acres%20of%20rural%20land%20%E2%80%94%20right%20next%20to%20one%20of%20America's%20most%20historic%20battlegrounds%20%E2%80%94%20with%2023%20million%20square%20feet%20of%20data%20centers.%3Cp%3EThe%20Washington%20Post%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20Ghadban's%2055%20acres%20on%20Pageland%20Lane%20now%20stand%20two%20115-foot-tall%20transmission%20towers%2C%20connected%20to%20250-foot-long%20transmission%20lines%2C%20which%20were%20erected%20during%20an%20upgrade%20by%20Dominion%20Energy%2C%20in%20part%20to%20accommodate%20all%20the%20machines%20in%20Data%20Center%20Alley.%20For%20Ghadban%2C%20the%20data%20center%20takeover%20of%20Prince%20William%20County%20is%20already%20here.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EBut%20with%20the%20Digital%20Gateway%2C%20she%20says%20the%20county%20could%20model%20a%20better%20way%20for%20this%20fast-expanding%20industry%20to%20build%20%E2%80%94%20one%20that%20takes%20up%20less%20land%20and%20is%20farther%20removed%20from%20things%20like%20housing%20and%20schools.%20According%20to%20QTS%2C%20Prince%20William%20County%20has%20set%20stricter%20standards%20for%20the%20Digital%20Gateway%C2%A0%20than%20any%20other%20jurisdiction%20where%20QTS%20has%20operated.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20it's%20going%20to%20set%20the%20precedent%20for%2C%20obviously%2C%20this%20development%20as%20well%20as%20many%20others%20around%20the%20country%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20QTS%20executive%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3Cstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20while%20companies%20trumpet%20the%20benefits%20of%20their%20data%20centers%2C%20they%20sometimes%20go%20to%20great%20lengths%20to%20keep%20the%20downsides%20a%20secret.%20To%20keep%20their%20machines%20from%20overheating%2C%20for%20example%2C%20data%20centers%20often%20consume%20and%20evaporate%20millions%20of%20gallons%20of%20water%20a%20day.%20What%20makes%20the%20problem%20tough%20to%20track%20%E2%80%94%20and%2C%20therefore%2C%20invisible%20to%20local%20residents%20%E2%80%94%20is%20companies%20rarely%20disclose%20just%20how%20much%20water%20any%20single%20data%20center%20is%20consuming.%20In%20The%20Dalles%2C%20a%20city%20in%20Oregon%2C%20Google%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Fabout%2Fdatacenters%2Flocations%2Fthe-dalles%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eglamorizes%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20plumes%20of%20water%20vapor%20that%20rise%20above%20the%20cooling%20towers%20for%20its%20data%20centers%20and%20%26quot%3Bcreate%20a%20quiet%20mist%20at%20dusk.%26quot%3B%20But%20when%20a%20local%20newspaper%20sought%20public%20records%20on%20how%20much%20water%20the%20data%20centers%20consume%20in%20the%20process%20of%20creating%20that%20mist%2C%20the%20city%20fought%20the%20request%20in%20court%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0with%20Google%20paying%20its%20legal%20bills.%20Last%20year%2C%20when%20the%20case%20finally%20settled%2C%20residents%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.oregonlive.com%2Fsilicon-forest%2F2022%2F12%2Fgoogles-water-use-is-soaring-in-the-dalles-records-show-with-two-more-data-centers-to-come.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elearned%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20Google%20is%20responsible%20for%20more%20than%20a%20quarter%20of%20the%20city's%20water%20use.%20Worldwide%2C%20according%20to%20site-specific%20data%20Google%20finally%20disclosed%2C%20its%20data%20centers%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fblog.google%2Foutreach-initiatives%2Fsustainability%2Four-commitment-to-climate-conscious-data-center-cooling%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Econsumed%3C%2Fa%3E%204.3%20billion%20gallons%20of%20water%20in%202021.%20(Google%20didn't%20respond%20to%20requests%20for%20comment.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%20there's%20the%20question%20of%20jobs.%20The%20industry%20says%20a%20single%20data%20center%20can%20create%20thousands%20of%20construction%20jobs%20over%20the%20course%20of%20the%20buildout%2C%20which%20in%20turn%20fuels%20more%20economic%20activity%20at%20local%20businesses%20and%20drives%20job%20growth.%20But%20opponents%20of%20data%20centers%20point%20out%20that%20for%20all%20the%20land%20they%20consume%2C%20they%20directly%20employ%20only%20a%20few%20dozen%20to%20a%20few%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.uschamber.com%2Fassets%2Farchived%2Fimages%2Fctec_datacenterrpt_lowres.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehundred%3C%2Fa%3E%20people%20after%20construction%20is%20complete.%20Take%20Meta%2C%20which%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eis%20currently%20building%20its%20biggest%20data%20center%20complex%20ever%2C%20spanning%20more%20than%205%20million%20square%20feet%20in%20Altoona%2C%20Iowa.%20When%20it's%20finished%2C%20the%20campus%20will%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatacenters.atmeta.com%2Fall-locations%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eemploy%3C%2Fa%3E%20just%20over%20400%20employees.%20By%20contrast%2C%20the%20Mall%20of%20America%2C%20which%20is%20just%20slightly%20bigger%20than%20Meta's%20data%20center%20complex%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mallofamerica.com%2Fupload%2FFactSheets_2016.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eemploys%3C%2Fa%3E%20some%2011%2C000%20people.%20Even%20the%20average%20Amazon%20fulfillment%20center%2C%20which%20encompasses%20only%20800%2C000%20square%20feet%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aboutamazon.com%2Fworkplace%2Ffacilities%23%3A~%3Atext%3DAround%2520800%252C000%2520square%2520feet%2520in%2Cbooks%252C%2520toys%252C%2520and%2520housewares.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eemploy%3C%2Fa%3Es%20around%201%2C500%20people%20%E2%80%94%C2%A023%20times%20more%20jobs%20per%20square%20foot%20than%20Meta's%20center%20in%20Altoona.%20If%20you're%20looking%20for%20employment%2C%20you%20probably%20won't%20find%20it%20in%20a%20data%20center.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECritics%20fear%20that%20turning%20your%20town%20into%20a%20corridor%20for%20data%20centers%20can%20also%20discourage%20the%20sort%20of%20business%20development%20that%20%3Cem%3Ewould%3C%2Fem%3E%20directly%20employ%20a%20lot%20of%20people.%20When%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Farizona-running-out-of-water-data-centers-blame-microsoft-google-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMesa%2C%20Arizona%3C%2Fa%3E%20invested%20in%20its%20power%20grid%20and%20broadband%20fiber%2C%20it%20hoped%20to%20attract%20advanced%20manufacturing%20facilities%20to%20the%20area.%20Instead%2C%20says%20Scott%20Somers%2C%20a%20city%20council%20member%2C%20the%20town%20has%20been%20%26quot%3Binundated%26quot%3B%20with%20what%20he%20calls%20%26quot%3Bwarehouses%20of%20ones%20and%20zeroes%2C%26quot%3B%20leaving%20few%20places%20for%20jobs-rich%20businesses%20to%20expand.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20data%20centers%20use%20up%20all%20the%20power%20or%20the%20water%20or%20the%20land%20in%20the%20community%2C%26quot%3B%20Somers%20says%2C%20%26quot%3Bthen%20where%20are%20we%20going%20to%20put%20other%20developments%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20account%20for%20the%20swelling%20energy%20consumption%20demanded%20by%20their%20data%20centers%2C%20tech%20giants%20have%20also%20become%20the%20largest%20investors%20in%20new%20sources%20of%20renewable%20energy.%20Last%20year%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fabout.bnef.com%2Fblog%2Fcorporations-brush-aside-energy-crisis-buy-record-clean-power%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20BloombergNEF%2C%20Amazon%2C%20Meta%2C%20Google%2C%20and%20Microsoft%20were%20the%20top%20four%20global%20purchasers%20of%20clean%20energy.%20Microsoft%20has%20even%20signed%20an%20ambitious%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theverge.com%2F2023%2F5%2F10%2F23717332%2Fmicrosoft-nuclear-fusion-power-plant-helion-purchase-agreement%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edeal%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20purchase%20energy%20from%20a%20nuclear%20fusion%20facility%20by%202028.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20big%20new%20investments%20in%20renewable%20energy%20aren't%20enough%20to%20keep%20up%20with%20power%20demands.%20Data%20centers%20operate%20at%20full%20speed%20every%20day%2C%20around%20the%20clock%2C%20even%20when%20the%20sun%20isn't%20shining%20and%20the%20wind%20isn't%20blowing.%20That%20means%20they%20often%20have%20to%20rely%20on%20other%2C%20dirtier%20sources%20of%20energy.%20Meta%2C%20for%20example%2C%20says%20it%20offsets%20100%25%20of%20its%20annual%20energy%20usage%20with%20renewable%20energy.%20But%20Ben%20Lee%2C%20a%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Pennsylvania%20who%20specializes%20in%20computer%20architecture%20and%20energy%20efficiency%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.seas.upenn.edu%2F~leebcc%2Fdocuments%2Facun23-explorer.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efound%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20Meta's%20energy%20consumption%20on%20an%20hourly%20basis%20in%202021%20was%20carbon-free%20only%20half%20the%20time.%20Google%20has%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsustainability.google%2Fprogress%2Fenergy%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%2C%20hour-to-hour%2C%20it%20is%20able%20to%20use%20carbon-free%20energy%20only%2064%25%20of%20the%20time.%20While%20it's%20undoubtedly%20a%20good%20thing%20that%20these%20companies%20are%20offsetting%20their%20emissions%20by%20adding%20new%20renewable%20energy%20to%20the%20grid%2C%20Lee%20says%2C%20%26quot%3BYour%20actual%20usage%20is%20only%20as%20green%20or%20brown%20as%20your%20local%20transmission%20lines.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20December%2012%2C%20hundreds%20of%20residents%20of%20Prince%20William%20County%20cycled%20in%20and%20out%20of%20the%20drab%20government%20hearing%20room%20where%20the%20local%20Board%20of%20Supervisors%20was%20meeting%20to%20decide%20the%20fate%20of%20the%20Digital%20Gateway%20project.%20One%20by%20one%2C%20over%2027%20tedious%20hours%2C%20they%20approached%20the%20hot%20pink%20microphone%20to%20plead%20with%20the%20weary%20board%20members.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESupporters%20accused%20opponents%20of%20being%20elitist%2C%20NIMBY%20obstructionists%2C%20hell%20bent%20on%20ruining%20a%20golden%20opportunity%20for%20the%20entire%20county.%20Opponents%20framed%20supporters%20as%20mercenary%20sellouts%20attempting%20to%20pad%20their%20own%20retirement%20funds%20at%20the%20expense%20of%20their%20neighbors.%20There%20were%20costumes%20and%20props%20and%20one%20particularly%20cringe%20adaptation%20of%20Joni%20Mitchell's%20%26quot%3BBig%20Yellow%20Taxi.%26quot%3B%20(%26quot%3BThey%20paved%20paradise%2C%20and%20put%20up%20a%20data%20center.%20Oooh.%20Stop.%20Stop.%20Stop.%26quot%3B)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20region's%20Civil%20War%20roots%20loomed%20large%20over%20the%20meeting.%20One%20Black%20woman%20speaking%20on%20behalf%20of%20her%20father%20%E2%80%94%20whose%2035-acre%20property%20has%20been%20in%20the%20family%20since%201876%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0told%20the%20board%20that%20opponents%20like%20Schlossberg%20have%20no%20right%20interfering%20in%20her%20family's%20decision%20to%20sell%20their%20land%20to%20the%20data%20centers.%20%26quot%3BMy%20ancestors%20toiled%20and%20farmed%20this%20land%20for%20decades%20to%20try%20to%20provide%20for%20their%20children%20and%20their%20grandchildren%20like%20me%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20the%20board.%20%26quot%3BShame%20on%20these%20know-it-alls%20trying%20to%20lecture%20you%20on%20what%20we%20should%20do%20with%20our%20family's%20land.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20the%20time%20Schlossberg%20spoke%2C%20it%20was%20after%201%3A30%20a.m.%20After%20handing%20out%20kitschy%20Hanukkah%20gifts%20as%20a%20peace%20offering%20to%20the%20board%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0an%20owl%20for%20wisdom%2C%20gelt%20to%20remind%20them%20%26quot%3Bthere%20are%20more%20important%20things%20than%20money%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20she%20urged%20them%20to%20consider%20the%20Digital%20Gateway's%20impact%20on%20their%20own%20legacy.%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20going%20to%20be%20your%20mistake%2C%20that%20you're%20going%20to%20have%20to%20apologize%20for%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20warned%20them.%20%26quot%3BThere%20is%20an%20off%20ramp.%20Take%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20board%20didn't%20take%20it.%20Instead%2C%20in%20a%20straight%20party-line%20vote%2C%20they%20approved%20the%20Digital%20Gateway.%20The%20Democratic%20majority%20voted%20in%20favor%2C%20the%20Republican%20minority%20against.%20One%20board%20member%20abstained%20to%20break%20the%20tie.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20be%20fair%2C%20there's%20only%20so%20much%20that%20local%20opposition%20can%20do%20to%20stem%20the%20global%20tide%20of%20data%20centers.%20Unlike%20crypto%20mining%2C%20another%20energy-sucking%20industry%20that%20has%20inspired%20widespread%20resistance%2C%20data%20centers%20are%20essential%20to%20the%20way%20the%20modern%20world%20works.%20They%20power%20our%20hospitals%20and%20governments%20as%20much%20as%20our%20TikToks%20and%20Midjourney%20masterpieces.%20In%202019%2C%20Singapore%20imposed%20a%20three-year%20moratorium%20on%20new%20data%20centers%2C%20and%20the%20Dutch%20government%20recently%20instituted%20its%20own%20nine-month%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rijksoverheid.nl%2Factueel%2Fnieuws%2F2022%2F02%2F16%2Fkabinet-besluit-tot-aanscherping-regels-hyperscale-datacenters%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emoratorium%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20hyperscalers.%20But%20countries%20that%20forbid%20data%20centers%20from%20opening%20are%20risking%20their%20own%20role%20in%20the%20future%20economy.%20%26quot%3BGrowth%20eventually%20will%20leap%20frog%20you%20if%20you%20don't%20allow%20it%20and%20manage%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Clower%2C%20the%20public%20policy%20expert.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20AI%20is%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20poised%20to%20make%20data%20centers%20more%20plentiful%20and%20powerful%2C%20what%20matters%20now%20is%20not%20wishing%20them%20away%2C%20but%20finding%20new%2C%20less%20destructive%20ways%20for%20them%20to%20grow.%20That%20starts%20with%20requiring%20the%20companies%20that%20run%20them%20to%20share%20more%20information%20about%20the%20resources%20their%20AI%20models%20are%20consuming.%20%26quot%3BThe%20minimum%20we%20should%20ask%20for%20is%20transparency%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Sasha%20Luccioni%2C%20a%20research%20scientist%20and%20climate%20lead%20at%20Hugging%20Face%2C%20a%20platform%20for%20AI%20developers.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20equally%20important%20part%20of%20the%20solution%20is%20asking%20ourselves%20a%20more%20fundamental%20question%3A%20Do%20we%20really%20need%20to%20use%20such%20immensely%20powerful%20AI%20models%20for%20every%20single%20daily%20chore%3F%20The%20corporate%20rush%20to%20pack%20these%20models%20into%20just%20about%20every%20product%20is%20the%20technological%20equivalent%20of%20hiring%20a%20team%20of%20bodybuilders%20to%20pick%20up%20your%20kids'%20Legos.%20%26quot%3BYou%20don't%20need%20to%20ask%20your%20fridge%20for%20a%20recipe%20for%20chocolate%20chip%20cookies%2C%26quot%3B%20Luccioni%20says.%20%26quot%3BYou%20can%20literally%20do%20a%20Google%20search.%20Switching%20out%20a%20model%20that%20will%20find%20you%20information%20on%20the%20internet%20to%20one%20that%20will%20generate%20your%20information%20is%20just%20using%20more%20energy%20for%20the%20same%20task.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20end%2C%20though%2C%20opponents%20of%20new%20technologies%20have%20seldom%20had%20much%20success%20at%20convincing%20consumers%20to%20forgo%20the%20Latest%20Cool%20Thing%20in%20the%20name%20of%20broader%20social%20concerns.%C2%A0When%20we've%20spent%20so%20long%20detached%20from%20the%20physical%20reality%20of%20the%20digital%20world%2C%20it%20makes%20it%20a%20lot%20easier%20to%20just%20ignore%20the%20environmental%20and%20human%20costs.%20Misbelieving%20that%20the%20internet%20simply%20exists%20somewhere%20out%20there%20in%20the%20cloud%20has%20rendered%20us%20unprepared%20to%20grapple%20with%20what%20happens%20when%20it%20all%20comes%20crashing%20down%20to%20earth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fissie-lapowsky%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EIssie%20Lapowsky%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20freelance%20journalist%20covering%20tech%2C%20politics%2C%20and%20society.%20Her%20work%20has%20been%20featured%20in%20The%20New%20York%20Times%2C%20Wired%2C%20and%20Fast%20Company.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-data-centers-land-grab-google-meta-openai-amazon-2023-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703156041000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65835bffa79e5746976be8df%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-data-centers-land-grab-google-meta-openai-amazon-2023-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Inside%20AI's%20giant%20land%20grab%20%E2%80%94%20and%20what%20it%20means%20for%20the%20future%20of%20humanity.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Issie%20Lapowsky)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-data-centers-land-grab-google-meta-openai-amazon-2023-12%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%2