he%20street%20signs%20and%20menus%20in%20restaurants.%20If%20they%20didn't%20speak%20English%2C%20a%20store%20clerk%20went%20out%20of%20the%20way%20to%20find%20someone%20who%20could%20speak%20English%20and%20help%20translate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYokohama%20was%20so%20safe%20that%20I%20took%20public%20buses%20by%20myself%20at%208%20to%20meet%20friends%20in%20different%20parts%20of%20the%20city.%20Attending%20an%20international%20school%20eased%20the%20transition%2C%20as%20we%20weren't%20exposed%20to%20the%20rigorous%20Japanese%20education%20system%2C%20which%20included%20long%20hours%2C%20school%20on%20Saturdays%2C%20and%20rigid%20testing%20systems.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShopping%20was%20generally%20an%20entirely%20different%20experience.%20Stationery%20stores%20were%20filled%20with%20rows%20upon%20rows%20of%20colorful%20glitter%20gel%20pens%20and%20erasers%20shaped%20like%20every%20food%20item%20and%20animal%20imaginable.%20I%20swapped%20out%20my%20favorite%20American%20brands%20for%20some%20of%20the%20colorful%2C%20eccentric%20street%20styles%20of%20Japan%20in%20the%20late%20'90s%20and%20early%202000s%20%E2%80%94%20perhaps%20the%20most%20notable%20being%20high-platform%20sneakers%20with%20shapes%20cut%20out%20of%20the%20wedge.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EI%20wasn't%20a%20fan%20of%20sushi%20but%20found%20food%20I%20loved%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFinding%20some%20of%20our%20favorite%20Western%20foods%20in%20grocery%20stores%20proved%20challenging.%20The%20goods%20that%20were%20available%20in%20specialty%20stores%20came%20at%20a%20premium%20price.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20too%20keen%20on%20sushi%2C%20sashimi%2C%20or%20many%20of%20the%20other%20seafood-centric%20Japanese%20delicacies%20at%20my%20young%20age%2C%20I%20learned%20to%20eat%20a%20lot%20of%20rice%2C%20ramen%2C%20and%20tempura.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20I%20could%20no%20longer%20find%20my%20favorite%20American%20sweets%2C%20I%20came%20to%20love%20iconic%20Japanese%20candies%20and%20snacks%2C%20from%20seaweed-covered%20rice%20crackers%20and%20Pocky%20to%20all%20the%20funky%2C%20fruity%20candies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20have%20distinct%20memories%20of%20my%20mom%20and%20I%20buying%20mystery%20pastries%20at%20a%20bakery%2C%20anticipating%20a%20custard%20or%20cream%20filling%20and%20instead%20biting%20into%20a%20red-bean%20curd%20or%20an%20octopus%20ball.%20All%20the%20details%20were%20part%20of%20the%20fun%2C%20though%2C%20and%20live%20on%20as%20favorite%20memories.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EIt%20was%20harder%20on%20my%20parents%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20most%20drastic%20challenges%20fell%20on%20my%20parents.%20Years%20later%2C%20I%20look%20back%20with%20a%20deep%20appreciation%20for%20them%2C%20particularly%20my%20mother%2C%20and%20how%20they%20took%20the%20move%20in%20stride.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20had%20to%20adapt%20to%20a%20new%20country%20and%20language%2C%20leave%20family%20and%20friends%20behind%2C%20start%20new%20jobs%2C%20and%20find%20a%20new%20home%2C%20all%20while%20navigating%20the%20challenges%20my%20brother%20and%20I%20faced%20with%20a%20new%20school%2C%20living%20out%20of%20a%20hotel%20until%20we%20found%20a%20house%2C%20and%20finding%20food%20to%20make%20us%20lunches.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESimple%20things%20we%20took%20for%20granted%2C%20including%20driving%2C%20came%20with%20a%20big%20learning%20curve.%20My%20mom%20has%20told%20the%20story%20numerous%20times%20that%20it%20took%20her%20four%20tries%20to%20pass%20her%20driver's%20test%20in%20Japan.%20She%20had%20to%20take%20it%20to%20obtain%20a%20Japanese%20license%20%E2%80%94%20a%20process%20that%20reflected%20the%20perfectionist%20culture%20there.%20Once%2C%20she%20automatically%20failed%20the%20test%20for%20stopping%20just%20over%20the%20line.%20Not%20to%20mention%2C%20once%20she%20passed%2C%20she%20had%20to%20navigate%20the%20narrow%20roads%2C%20congested%20traffic%2C%20driving%20on%20the%20left%20side%20of%20the%20road%2C%20and%20reading%20road%20signs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELearning%20that%20my%20family%20was%20moving%20us%20to%20Japan%20was%20one%20of%20the%20mos