O%20Data%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F01%2F28134446%2F3891925784_eb02c9d8e3_o.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3ESignalling%20a%20downturn%20in%20the%20labour%20market%2C%20fresh%20formal%20employment%20creation%20in%20October%20declined%20by%2016.7%25%20in%20comparison%20to%20September.%20While%20the%20number%20of%20jobs%20created%20in%20September%20stood%20at%209%2C26%2C%20934%2C%20the%20number%20reduced%20to%207%2C72%2C084%20in%20October%2C%20according%20to%20the%20latest%20payroll%20data%20released%20by%20the%20Employees%E2%80%99%20Provident%20Fund%20Organisation%20(EPFO).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20EPFO%20payroll%20data%20helps%20to%20track%20employment%20creation%20in%20the%20formal%20sector%2C%20as%20every%20new%20employee%20must%20sign%20up%20for%20a%20provident%20fund%20under%20the%20EPFO.%20The%20National%20Statistical%20Office%20(NSO)%20too%20uses%20the%20EPFO%20data%20to%20analyse%20employment%20trends%20in%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAround%2068.7%25%20(5%2C30%2C884)%20of%20the%20total%207%2C72%2C084%20who%20joined%20the%20workforce%20in%20October%20were%20in%20the%20age%20group%20of%2018-28%20age%2C%20accounting%20for%20the%20highest%20among%20new%20EPF%20subscribers%20in%20October.%20The%20same%20figure%20had%20stood%20at%2068.5%25%20in%20the%20previous%20month%20of%20September%2C%20%3Cem%3EBusiness%20Standard%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Findustry%2Fnews%2Ffresh-formal-job-creation-dips-to-7-month-low-in-october-shows-epfo-data-123122001097_1.html%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0quoting%20official%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20those%20who%20joined%20the%20workforce%20and%20registered%20themselves%20as%20new%20EPF%20subscribers%20in%20the%20age%20group%20above%2035%20reduced%20from%2016.1%25%20in%20September%20to%2015.9%25%20in%20October.%20Women%E2%80%99s%20share