he-war-on-drugs-has-failed-13034912%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22In%20Absence%20of%2097%20Suspended%20Opposition%20MPs%2C%20Lok%20Sabha%20Passes%20Three%20Criminal%20Bills%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F20204302%2FLS-votes.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cspan%3E%20In%20the%20absence%20of%20the%2097%20opposition%20MPs%20who%20have%20been%20suspended%2C%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20on%20Wednesday%20(December%2020)%20passed%20the%20three%20new%20criminal%20Bills.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20three%20new%20Bills%20include%20the%20Bharatiya%20Nyaya%20Sanhita%20Bill%20to%20replace%20the%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%2C%201860%3B%20the%20Bharatiya%20Sakshya%20Adhiniyam%20Bill%20to%20replace%20the%20Indian%20Evidence%20Act%2C%201872%3B%20and%20the%20Bharatiya%20Nagarik%20Suraksha%20Sanhita%20Bill%20to%20replace%20the%20Criminal%20Procedure%20Code%2C%201973.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Bills%20were%20first%20taken%20up%20for%20passage%20and%20consideration%20on%20Tuesday%2C%20hours%20after%2049%20opposition%20MPs%20were%20suspended%20from%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20following%20protests%20in%20the%20house%20demanding%20a%20statement%20from%20Union%20home%20minister%20Amit%20Shah%20on%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fparliament-security-breach-anniversary-slogan-dictatorship%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Esecurity%20breach%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20parliament%20last%20week.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20Wednesday%2C%20as%20the%20debate%20continued%20in%20the%20afternoon%2C%20it%20was%20paused%20for%20a%20few%20minutes%20as%20parliamentary%20affairs%20minister%20Pralhad%20Joshi%20came%20in%20to%20announce%20the%20suspension%20of%20two%20more%20opposition%20MPs.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESince%20December%2014%2C%20a%20total%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2F141-here-are-all-the-mps-suspended-from-parliament-this-winter-session%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E143%20opposition%20MPs%20have%20been%20suspended%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20total%20of%2035%20MPs%20participated%20in%20the%20debate%20over%20the%20three%20new%20criminal%20Bills%20over%20the%20course%20of%20the%20two%20days%20(Tuesday%20and%20Wednesday).%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20debate%20saw%20the%20participation%20of%20MPs%20from%20the%20ruling%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)%20and%20parliamentarians%20from%20parties%20friendly%20to%20it%20like%20the%20Biju%20Janata%20Dal%2C%20Rashtriya%20Lok%20Janshakti%20Party%20and%20the%20YSR%20Congress%20Party%2C%20who%20also%20supported%20the%20legislation.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOnly%20MPs%20from%20the%20All%20India%20Majlis-e-Ittehadul%20Muslimeen%20(AIMIM)%20and%20the%20Shiromani%20Akali%20Dal%20(SAD)%20raised%20concerns%20about%20the%20Bills%20bringing%20in%20a%20%E2%80%9Cpolice%20state%E2%80%9D%20giving%20the%20government%20unbridled%20power.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESAD%20MP%20Harsimrat%20Kaur%20raised%20the%20absence%20of%20the%20opposition%20during%20her%20speech%20and%20said%20that%20the%20laws%20will%20give%20%E2%80%9Cunbridled%20powers%20to%20the%20police%E2%80%9D%20and%C2%A0create%20an%20authoritarian%20state%2C%C2%A0adding%C2%A0that%20powers%20are%20being%20given%20without%20%E2%80%9Cany%20checks%20and%20balances%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22MPs'%20Job%20Is%20to%20Ask%20for%20Accountability.%20Shutting%20Them%20Down%20Is%20No%20Answer.%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fmp-suspensions-accountability-parliament-attack%5C%22%3EMPs%E2%80%99%20Job%20Is%20to%20Ask%20for%20Accountability.%20Shutting%20Them%20Down%20Is%20No%20Answer.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThese%20arbitrary%20powers%20are%20against%20liberty%2C%20democracy%2C%20dissent%20and%20opposition.%20Here%20is%20a%20living%20example%20that%20such%20an%20important%20Bill%20is%20being%20discussed%2C%20which%20should%20be%20in%20a%20fair%20and%20transparent%20manner%20with%20everybody%20allowed%20to%20air%20their%20views%2C%20and%20here%20there%20is%20only%20the%20ruling%20party%20and%20a%20handful%20of%20us%20opposition%20who%20are%20being%20allowed%20to%20say%20what%20we%20want%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20is%20not%20the%20way%20for%20such%20an%20important%20Bill%20to%20be%20passed.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESAD%20(Amritsar)%20MP%20Simranjit%20Singh%20Mann%20also%20said%20that%20this%20was%20an%20%E2%80%9Cundemocratic%20practice%20of%20debating%20these%20Bills%20because%20the%20opposition%20is%20not%20present.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThey%20are%20also%20unconstitutional%3B%20again%2C%20because%20the%20opposition%20is%20not%20present%20and%20I%20propose%20that%20these%20Bills%20come%20up%20when%20the%20whole%20opposition%20is%20present%20and%20it%20is%20properly%20debated.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMann%E2%80%99s%20speech%20was%20cut%20off%20when%20he%20raised%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fnijjar-pannun-modi-foreign-policy-national-interest%5C%22%3Ekilling%20of%20Sikh%20activist%20Hardeep%20Singh%20Nijjar%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Vancouver%2C%20Canada%20on%20June%2019%20and%20referred%20to%20it%20as%20an%20important%20%E2%80%9Ccriminal%20%5Bmatter%5D%E2%80%9D.%20The%20chair%2C%20Rajendra%20Agarwal%2C%20said%20Mann%20was%20%E2%80%9Cdeviating%E2%80%9D%20from%20the%20topic%20and%20asked%20the%20next%20speaker%20to%20start%20speaking.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAIMIM%20MP%20Asaduddin%20Owaisi%20also%20opposed%20the%20Bills%20and%20said%20that%20they%20would%20increase%20the%20powers%20of%20the%20police%20and%20the%20government%20in%20the%20name%20of%20bringing%20in%20reforms.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CIf%20Bhagat%20Singh%20and%20Mohandas%20Karamchand%20Gandhi%20were%20alive%2C%20they%20would%20say%20that%20this%20is%20the%20Rowlatt%20Act.%20The%20government%20has%20to%20answer%20who%20are%20the%20actual%20successors%20of%20Macaulay%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHe%20also%20raised%20concerns%20about%20the%20clauses%20of%20the%20Unlawful%20Activities%20(Prevention)%20Act%20(UAPA)%20being%20included%20in%20the%20laws%20and%20said%20that%20minorities%2C%20Dalits%20and%20Adivasis%20are%20facing%20disproportionate%20convictions%20and%20detentions%2C%20but%20laws%20are%20being%20reformed%20to%20favour%20the%20powerful.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FnpHbecvfc9o%3Fsi%3D30HSRD3Jxzx7lC7R%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CMuslims%2C%20Dalits%2C%20Adivasis%20are%20languishing%20in%20jail.%20They%20are%20reforming%20the%20laws%20for%20the%20powerful.%20How%20will%20the%20poor%20benefit%20from%20this%3F%20The%20cure%20%5Bthe%20new%20laws%5D%20is%20deadlier%20than%20the%20disease%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20his%20reply%20to%20the%20house%20at%20the%20close%20of%20the%20discussion%20on%20Tuesday%2C%20Shah%20said%20that%20the%20new%20laws%20have%20been%20drafted%20keeping%20in%20mind%20the%20spirit%20of%20the%20Indian%20constitution.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CPrime%20Minister%20Modi%20promised%20from%20the%20ramparts%20of%20the%20Red%20Fort%20that%20the%20country%20will%20be%20liberated%20from%20colonial%20laws%2C%20and%20the%20home%20ministry%20has%20sought%20to%20do%20that.%20These%20%5Bold%5D%20laws%20were%20to%20govern%20a%20dependent%20country%2C%20but%20the%20new%20laws%20have%20been%20framed%20keeping%20in%20mind%20the%20core%20values%20of%20our%20constitution%20%E2%80%93%20individual%20freedom%2C%20human%20rights%20and%20equal%20treatment%20for%20all%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Shah.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20a%20veiled%20reference%20to%20the%20opposition%20and%20the%20Congress%2C%20Shah%20said%20that%20those%20who%20had%20raised%20objections%20saying%20that%20there%20is%20not%20much%20change%20in%20the%20new%20laws%2C%20need%20to%20understand%20the%20laws%20as%20Indians.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CFor%20the%20first%20time%2C%20laws%20are%20going%20to%20be%20made%20according%20to%20the%20spirit%20of%20our%20constitution%20under%20the%20leadership%20of%20Modi%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Eji%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20I%20am%20proud%20to%20have%20changed%20these%20three%20laws%20after%20150%20years.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHe%20continued%3A%20%E2%80%9CSome%20people%20used%20to%20say%20that%20we%20do%20not%20understand%20them%3B%20I%20tell%20them%20that%20if%20you%20keep%20your%20mind%20as%20an%20Indian%2C%20then%20you%20will%20understand.%20But%20if%20there%20is%20Italy%20in%20your%20mind%2C%20you%20will%20never%20understand.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EShah%20said%20that%20for%20the%20first%20time%2C%20terrorism%20has%20been%20defined%20in%20criminal%20laws.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20had%20promised%20to%20ensure%20zero%20tolerance%20to%20terror.%20There%20was%20no%20definition%20of%20terrorism.%20I%20am%20astonished%20at%20how%20some%20people%20are%20trying%20to%20defend%20and%20save%20the%20lives%20of%20terrorists%20in%20the%20name%20of%20%E2%80%98human%20rights%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CTerrorism%20is%20the%20biggest%20threat%20to%20human%20rights.%20Remember%2C%20this%20is%20neither%20the%20rule%20of%20the%20British%20nor%20of%20the%20Congress.%20This%20is%20the%20rule%20of%20BJP%20and%20Modi%20ji.%20No%20arguments%20to%20save%20terrorists%20will%20be%20entertained%20here.%20To%20ensure%20that%20it%20is%20not%20misused%2C%20we%20have%20defined%20it%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fas-laws-expand-their-reach-in-india-political-freedoms-shrink%5C%22%3EAs%20Laws%20Expand%20Their%20Reach%20in%20India%2C%20Political%20Freedoms%20Shrink%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EShah%20also%20said%20that%20the%20new%20legislations%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fsedition-law-repealed-three-new-bills-tabled-in-parliament-to-replace-criminal-laws%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eremove%20sedition%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20and%20that%20%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Erajdroh%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9D%20(sedition)%20has%20been%20replaced%20with%20%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Edeshdroh%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9D%20(anti-patriotic%20acts).%20He%20said%20that%20no%20one%20will%20be%20penalised%20for%20criticising%20the%20government%2C%20but%20will%20face%20punishment%20for%20acting%20against%20the%20country.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20is%20an%20independent%20country%2C%20nobody%20will%20be%20sent%20to%20jail%20for%20criticising%20the%20government%2C%20but%20you%20cannot%20say%20anything%20against%20the%20country%20or%20do%20anything%20against%20the%20interests%20of%20the%20country.%20If%20you%20harm%20the%20flag%20or%20the%20property%20of%20the%20country%2C%20you%20will%20be%20sent%20to%20jail%20%E2%80%93%20harsh%20punishment%20for%20harming%20the%20country%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHe%20also%20said%20that%20there%20is%20a%20%E2%80%9Cmisunderstanding%E2%80%9D%20on%20the%20increased%20period%20of%20police%20custody%20from%2015%20days%20to%2090%20days.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20is%20a%20misunderstanding.%20The%20total%20police%20custody%20is%2015%20days.%20There%20are%20some%20cases%20where%20the%20accused%20get%20admitted%20to%20a%20hospital%20during%20the%20initial%20days%20to%20avoid%20police%20custody.%20It%20is%20to%20address%20such%20practices%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EResponding%20to%20concerns%20raised%20by%20Owaisi%20that%20the%20new%20laws%20would%20turn%20the%20country%20into%20a%20%E2%80%9Cpolice%20state%E2%80%9D%20by%20giving%20unbridled%20powers%20to%20the%20police%20and%20the%20state%2C%20Shah%20said%20that%20the%20%E2%80%9Cthese%20laws%20are%20being%20made%20so%20there%20is%20no%20police%20state.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20three%20new%20Bills%20were%20first%20introduced%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20on%20August%2011.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThey%20were%20then%20referred%20to%20a%20parliamentary%20standing%20committee%2C%20which%20published%20its%20report%20on%20November%2010.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20report%20hailed%20the%20move%20to%20bring%20in%20the%20new%20Bills%20and%20recommended%20some%20changes.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESubsequently%2C%20the%20Bills%20were%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Funion-govt-withdraws-3-criminal-law-bills-to-make-changes-recommended-by-parl-panel%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ewithdrawn%20and%20reintroduced%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20during%20the%20winter%20session%20on%20December%2012.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWriting%20in%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20G.%20Mohan%20Gopal%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fsecond-avatar-criminal-law-bills-has-anything-changed%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Enoted%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20even%20in%20their%20redrafted%20form%2C%20the%20Bills%20%E2%80%9Cweaponise%20the%20police%20and%20the%20criminal%20justice%20system%20to%20give%20the%20political%20leadership%20at%20all%20levels%20%E2%80%93%20centre%2C%20state%20and%20local%20%E2%80%93%20even%20greater%20opportunity%20to%20abuse%20the%20criminal%20justice%20system%20for%20political%20gain%20through%20selective%2C%20targeted%20and%20politically%20biased%20prosecution%20against%20ideological%20and%20political%20rivals.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESome%20of%20the%20changes%20brought%20in%20the%20second%20draft%20include%20a%20pullback%20of%20the%20expansion%20of%20the%20crime%20of%20terrorism%20beyond%20the%20existing%20definition%20in%20the%20Unlawful%20Activities%20(Prevention)%20Act%2C%201967%20(UAPA)%3B%20and%20a%20circumscribed%20definition%20of%20%E2%80%9Cpetty%20organised%20crime%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20government%20has%20also%20dropped%20its%20earlier%20proposal%20that%20life%20imprisonment%20in%20all%20cases%20shall%20be%20%E2%80%9Cimprisonment%20for%20remainder%20of%20a%20person%E2%80%99s%20natural%20life%E2%80%9D%2C%20clarified%20punishment%20for%20%E2%80%98culpable%20homicide%20not%20amounting%20to%20murder%E2%80%99%20as%20well%20as%20the%20definition%20of%20community%20service%2C%20and%20brought%20in%20a%20distinction%20between%20mental%20illness%20and%20mental%20unsoundness%2C%20among%20other%20changes.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20parliamentary%20standing%20committee%E2%80%99s%20recommendation%20that%20adultery%20be%20maintained%20as%20a%20gender-neutral%20crime%20has%20not%20been%20included%20in%20the%20new%20version%20of%20the%20legislations.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20addition%2C%20other%20committee%20recommendations%20that%20have%20not%20found%20a%20place%20are%20that%20non-consensual%20sexual%20acts%20covered%20by%20IPC%20Section%20377%20continue%20to%20be%2